definitions.definition: Any of various freshwater crayfish , typically of the genus Cherax , valued as food, especially Cherax destructor of southeastern Australia.
A species of marine ghost shrimp , Trypaea australiensis , widely harvested by recreational anglers as bait ; a nipper .

main_definition: ( Australia ) Any of various freshwater crayfish , typically of the genus Cherax , valued as food, especially Cherax destructor of southeastern Australia. [from 19th c.]
secondary_definitions: ( Australia , chiefly Queensland ) A species of marine ghost shrimp , Trypaea australiensis , widely harvested by recreational anglers as bait ; a nipper . [from 20th c.]
